<p><b>Octal</b> is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Numeral_syste=
m" title=3D"Numeral system">numeral system</a> for representing a numeric v=
alue as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radix" title=3D"Radix">bas=
e</a> 8. Generally, an octal digit is represented as "0" to "7" with the sa=
me value as for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Decimal" title=3D"=
Decimal">decimal</a> but with each place a power of 8. For example:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
